The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Berlin, April 15: Siemens AG is discussing the possible sale of its main telecommunications unit to Motorola Inc, a German newspaper reported today. Motorola has expressed interest in the unit, but Siemens wants to include other struggling units in any deal, the Frankfurter Allgemeine Sonntagszeitung said in a summary of an article to appear tomorrow. The newspaper said both companies had declined to comment. 

 Mumbai, April 15: Gold and silver prices touched new highs at the bullion market today. Silver zoomed by a whopping Rs 570 to Rs 19,890 and gold firmed up by Rs 30 to close at Rs 8,855 due to heavy buying in anticipation of steep rise in global prices.

 Hyderabad, April 15: DaimlerChrysler is hoping to increase its market share in India. The makers of Mercedes-Benz cars will focus on non-metro cities, according to Wilfried Aulbur, managing director and CEO of DaimlerChrysler India.




